    "full_text_markdown": "The paper investigates the current state and practices in biomedical image analysis competitions. It highlights that while knowledge exchange is a primary incentive for participation (70%), many participants face time constraints during method development (32%). The survey also reveals that 94% of solutions are deep learning-based, with 84% using standard architectures. Data processing challenges are common, addressed by patch-based training and downsampling. K-fold cross-validation was used by only 37%, and ensembling was performed by 50% of participants based on multiple identical or heterogeneous models. Postprocessing steps were applied in 48% of the cases."
